  <prompt>
    Replace the current ~11-tile Node Types left panel in the PlaybookBuilder canvas with a
    full 33-executor categorized selector. Categories are 6 tiers using integer prefixes:
    AI (0-9), Compute (10-19), Mutations (20-29), Control (30-39), Delivery (40-49),
    Capability (50+). Each entry shows: tier prefix + name + 1-line description sourced from
    the C# enum XML doc comments (parallel metadata via Wave 3 endpoint OR static TS metadata).
    Drag-drop a tile to create a node with the correct `sprk_executortype` Choice value.
    Component Justification (CLAUDE.md §11) applies — see constraints.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React + Fluent UI v9 developer. Familiar with @xyflow/react v12 node-creation flow,
    Zustand canvas store, and the existing `NODE_PALETTE` array in `BuilderLayout.tsx`.
    Goal: replace the existing palette with a categorized, scrollable, semantically-tokened panel.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Updated `src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/components/BuilderLayout.tsx` (or extracted
    `NodePalette.tsx` sub-component, preferred) that:
    1. Displays 33 executor entries grouped into 6 categorized tiers (collapsible group headers)
    2. Each entry: tier prefix (e.g., "01") + executor name + 1-line description
    3. Description source: either fetched from Wave 3 endpoint (`GET /api/ai/playbook-builder/executor-config-schemas`) OR a static TS metadata constant — fetched preferred to avoid drift
    4. Drag-drop creates a node with the correct `sprk_executortype` Choice value baked into node data
    5. All colors use Fluent v9 semantic tokens (ADR-021 binding)
    6. Tier groups collapsible/expandable; first-time user sees all 6 tiers expanded
    7. Search/filter input above the panel (small win — optional, but consistent with maker UX)
    8. Build passes (`npm run build:prod` per CLAUDE.md §12) with 0 errors / 0 new warnings
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-doc">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="current-layout">src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/components/BuilderLayout.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="canvas-types">src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/types/canvas.ts</file>
    <file purpose="canvas-store">src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/stores/canvasStore.ts</file>
    <file purpose="dataverse-sync">src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/services/playbookNodeSync.ts</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-006">Fluent UI v9 ONLY (`@fluentui/react-components`). No v8 patterns.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Dark mode binding. Use semantic tokens (`tokens.colorNeutralBackground1`, `tokens.colorNeutralForeground1`, etc.). NO hardcoded hex colors. Icons use `currentColor`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Not BFF — no publish-size verification. Code Page bundle size DOES matter, but no per-task ceiling defined.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-22">33-executor categorized panel with 6 tiers (AI 0-9, Compute 10-19, Mutations 20-29, Control 30-39, Delivery 40-49, Capability 50+).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-26">Node creation MUST set `sprk_executortype` Choice value on the new node — NO `sprk_nodetype` references in canvas state (this task is the primary new-node creation path; replaces old NODE_PALETTE).</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Component Justification triple for new `NodePalette.tsx` sub-component (if extracted):
      1. Existing: `BuilderLayout.tsx` has an inline `NODE_PALETTE` constant + render block (~11 tiles). It is part of BuilderLayout's layout responsibility.
      2. Extension: extracting to a dedicated `NodePalette.tsx` reduces BuilderLayout from ~400 LOC and makes the panel testable in isolation. Extension wins over keeping inline because the new panel is 33 entries with category state — significantly more complex than 11 flat tiles.
      3. Cost-of-doing-nothing: keeping inline keeps BuilderLayout >500 LOC and tangled. Tests for the panel become tests for the layout. UAT regression risk grows.
    </constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §12">Build command: `npm run build:prod` (NOT `npm run build`) per FAILURE-MODES AP-1.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>code-page/playbookbuilder</topic>
    <files>
