    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The current panel shows 11 named tiles (AI Analysis, AI Completion, Condition, etc.) hard-coded
      in `BuilderLayout.tsx`. R7 expands the model to 33 executors organized by tier. The categorized
      view helps makers discover the right executor without scrolling a flat list of 33 items.
      Tier prefix integers (01, 10, 20, 30, 40, 50+) match the `sprk_playbookexecutortype` Choice values
      and the C# enum values, so visual order matches dispatch ID order.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="024" status="prerequisite">Wave 2 dispatch refactor complete — orchestrator reads `sprk_executortype` single-hop.</dependency>
      <dependency task="033" status="ideal-not-blocking">Wave 3 endpoint (`GET /api/ai/playbook-builder/executor-config-schemas`) ideal for fetching descriptions. If not yet shipped, fall back to static TS metadata constant in this task and refetch dynamically in task 083.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 083 wires the typed-config-form renderer that consumes the same schemas.</item>
      <item>Task 086 promotes Action selection to dedicated Action tab — coordinated UI work.</item>
      <item>Task 088 replaces remaining `sprk_nodetype` references in canvas state (out-of-scope for this task; in-scope is new-node creation only).</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: code-page UI modification, tag code-page+ui, ADR-006+021 applicable, quality gates Step 9.5 required · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-22 + design.md §11 + audit doc (task 080) + `.claude/skills/fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Verify W2 task 024 complete">
      Confirm dispatch reform is in place. If not, STOP.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Check W3 task 033 endpoint status">
      If `GET /api/ai/playbook-builder/executor-config-schemas` is deployed, plan to fetch descriptions from it.
      Otherwise, plan to embed a static TS metadata constant (33 entries × {tier, name, description}) in `executorMetadata.ts` for this task — task 083 will move to fetched.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Extract NodePalette.tsx component">
      Create new file `src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/components/NodePalette.tsx`.
      Move the existing `NODE_PALETTE` constant + render block from `BuilderLayout.tsx` into the new component.
      Use Fluent v9 components: `Accordion` / `AccordionItem` for tier groups, `Card` or `Button` for tiles.
      Use Fluent v9 semantic tokens for all colors (ADR-021).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Implement 33-entry metadata">
      In `src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/config/executorMetadata.ts` (NEW file), define:
      ```
      export interface ExecutorMetadata { value: number; tier: 'AI'|'Compute'|'Mutations'|'Control'|'Delivery'|'Capability'; tierPrefix: string; name: string; description: string; }
      export const EXECUTOR_METADATA: ExecutorMetadata[] = [ /* 33 entries */ ];
      ```
      Tier mapping: 0-9=AI, 10-19=Compute, 20-29=Mutations, 30-39=Control, 40-49=Delivery, 50+=Capability.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Render categorized panel">
      In `NodePalette.tsx`:
      - Group `EXECUTOR_METADATA` by tier
      - Render an `Accordion` with 6 items (one per tier) — all expanded by default
      - Each tier item lists its executors as draggable tiles
      - Each tile shows: tierPrefix + name + description (truncated to 1 line, with tooltip for full text)
      - All colors via semantic tokens
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Wire drag-drop to canvas store">
      On drop, create a new node with:
      ```
      data.type = 'aiAnalysis'|'aiCompletion'|... (legacy discriminator for React Flow renderer)
      data.executorType = <Choice value> (NEW — bound to sprk_executortype on round-trip)
      ```
      Coordinate with task 088 (canvas state migration) — for now, set BOTH fields so this task's output doesn't regress existing rendering. Task 088 will retire `data.type` once canvas state migration completes.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Update BuilderLayout.tsx">
      Replace the inline palette render with `<NodePalette onNodeDrop={...} />`. Delete the now-unused `NODE_PALETTE` constant + `NodePaletteItem` interface.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Build">
      Run: `cd src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder && npm run build:prod` (NOT `npm run build` per AP-1).
      Goal: 0 errors, 0 new warnings.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on `NodePalette.tsx`, `executorMetadata.ts`, and modified `BuilderLayout.tsx`.
      Run `/adr-check` against ADR-006 (Fluent v9), ADR-021 (dark mode + semantic tokens).
      Verify NO hardcoded colors via Grep: `Grep` for `#fff`, `#000`, `rgb(`, `rgba(` in the new files.
      Fix findings.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 082 status complete; advance to next Wave 8 task.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      Commit new + modified files. Message:
      `feat(playbookbuilder/r7): categorized 33-executor Node Types panel (Wave 8 task 082, FR-22)`. No PR yet.
    </step>
  </steps>

